Zinhle Maditla stands accused of killing her four children by feeding them rat poison in December last year. JOHANNESBURG - Zinhle Maditla, the Klarinet mother who confessed to poisoning her four young children, is due back in the Emalahleni Magistrate's Court. Closing arguments are expected to be heard. READ: Gruesome details of Klarinet child murders emerge The court will also be told if police have verified an alternative address provided by Maditla's lawyers at her last court appearance. Maditla has confessed to murdering her four young children -- Minenhle (8), Blessing (6), Shaniqua (4) and 11-month-old Ethan. READ: Mom accused of murdering children applies for bail She's been in custody since December after handing herself over to police. Maditla wants to be released on bail while the state deals with her case.